description: After Daredevil is shot by Black Widow, Karen Page struggles to nurse him back to health. Once the Man Without Fear regains his senses, he’s hot on Widow’s trail! But this manhunt isn’t without obstacle; enter Ursa Major, Soviet Russia's strangest science project!
name: Widow's Kiss (Part 2)

description:
Woody is missing and the clock is ticking! If Quantum doesn't find him soon, they will both dissipate into pure energy. Could an old enemy be behind Woody's disappearance?

Time is running out. Woody is missing. Quantum suspects foul play. If Quantum doesn't find Woody soon, they're both royally screwed.
name: Tick, Tick, Tick

description: Monstergirl seduces Thunderhead disguised as Bonfire.
name: You'll Never Walk Alone into the Furnace of Unstable Molecules!
The Replacement God

description:
Aquaman opens up Poseidonis to tourism against Vulko's objections. One of Tsunami's old enemies, Rhombus, takes over a loser's body and comes looking for Deep Blue.

Several members of a large firm are attempting to convince Aquaman that opening Poseidonis to tourism will be extremely beneficial for the city overall,much to his immense skepticism but he agrees to take the offer into consideration. While in a city a man named Sam is struck and killed by a meteor,killing him. Aquaman,Vulko,Dolphin,Koryak, and Garth then attempt to decide on the best option but upon Deep Blue's approval Aquaman decides to try it out, while Aquaman excuses all but Vulko beginning a savage argument for Vulko abandoning the city, which all the others eavesdrop on.

While on land Sam arises from his grave calling for his wife Linda,which Tsunami senses. While back in the city the tourist trade thrives for the city. While Dolphin finally confronts Aquaman about each other, with her letting her know that there can be know us until she settles things with Aquaman.Aquaman then gives the couple his blessing and respect after she explains her fear of the darkness inside of him.While Sam tracks down and murders his ex-wife and her new husband. Sam then attacks Aquaman where Deep Blue reveals he is now Rhombus, before battling him and being defeated.
name: Open for Business

description: Green Lantern joins the battle, a new fantastic location is seen and the Injustice gang does more vile deeds! Aquaman, Flash and Kyle Rayner return to Earth and find out that things have gone wrong! Horrificly wrong!
name: Rock of Ages, Part 3: Wonderworld

description: Deadpool and Blind Al go to the aquarium (Al hates it). There Deadpool tells her if she can get out of the area before he counts to 200 and finds her, she's free to go. Al is unsure of his intentions thinking he is just playing with her and this will just get her hopes up for nothing. But she plays along and tries to escape. While they are playing hide and seek the Great Lakes Avengers stumble upon the scene and assume Deadpool is up to some villainy. They battle. During the fight Deadpool accidentally activates his teleportation belt and it is interfered with Doorman's mystic abilities and Deadpool and Blind Al are accidentally sent into the past!
name: Road-Trip Roulette!

description: Nettie has been keeping Zero up all night protecting the the streets of New Orleans. And with mysterious late night voodoo murders and cops at his doorstep, there doesn't seem to be any rest in sight.
name: The Buzz, Part 1

description:
Prison break! Rogue and Gambit battle Nanny for freedom!

In New York City, Maggott has traced Joseph's trail to the roof of the World Trade Center.

In the Antarctic caverns, Trish Tilby finds a de-powered Hank McCoy, while Remy LeBeau broods about his dark past.

On the streets of NYC, Maggott is accosted by Psylocke, while Archangel tries to find her.

The caverns: Rogue tries to make sense of the shadowy memories she had absorbed from Remy, while Joseph, having escaped his bonds, frees the rest.

NYC: the fight between Psylocke and Maggott continues. When Psylocke strikes him with a psychic knife, the feedback stuns her as well as Maggott, and he loses control over his slugs. Archangel arrives in time to bat back the creature.

The caverns: the X-Men and the bounty hunters try to find their way out, when Nanny arrives and converts to battle mode. But as Nanny is not equipped to sense normal humans, Trish Tilby decapitates the android with a crowbar.

determined to finally face his past, Gambit gives himself up to the bounty hunters.
name: The Crawl

description: Stormwatch Black investigates a small town in Louisiana that is being shielded by the American military. Meanwhile, Weatherman learns that I/O has been creating superhumans, illegally, in El Salvador and may be doing so in America as well.
name: Strange Weather, Two Of Three: Red Sky In The Morning

description:
Overview

It's the end of the world and the almighty First Father hath sent a plague of Aliens. Give your faith to him or face an eternity of damnation.
Luse's hunt for Cassy's killer leads him to a strip club to find Sergent William Perry and meets up with a couple of old friends.
name: Three: When the Mony Runs Out

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

description: Roque Ja escorts Smiley and Fone higher into the mountains, against their wills. The possum kids, who have been tracking them since they disappeared from the Barrelhaven compound days earlier, discover them in the company of Roque Ja and grow concerned for their safety. Knowing Roque Ja hates interlopers in his mountains, the possum kids and their raccoon friend Roderick lure the two stupid Rat Creatures to Roque Ja, causing them to fall off a cliff and giving the Bones a chance to escape. Roderick refuses to leave until he calls out for all of his other orphaned friends.
name: The Orphans

description: Story continued from Green Arrow (1987-1998 1st Series) #125. New York City stands on the brink of tearing itself apart and not even the combined efforts of Green Lantern and Green Arrow may be able to stop it. Story concludes in Green Arrow (1987-1998 1st Series) #126.
name: Hate Crimes Part 2: Fanning the Fire

description: "Sensitive Criminals" comes to a close as the final fate of The Invisibles circa 1924 is revealed, as well as even more bizarre secrets about the mysterious Hand of Glory.
name: Parisian Pierrot

description: It's a hot night in Gotham City, where the living is hard, but the dying is so easy for those willing to stay dead. The Dark Knight discovers that is not the case with one John Doe falls prey both to gangs and to Killer Croc and still keeps coming back for more.
name: Gotham D.O.A.
So What Happened To Power Girl?

description: Batman got them out of the predicament, and Nightwing exploded on him for encroaching on his new territory. Bruce left town. Roland Desmond enlisted the services of Lady Vic and a cowboy named Stallion. Dick regretted what he said to his mentor and called Alfred.
name: Dead Meat

description:
Brainiac 5 at last opens a portal to the time-lost Legion's 30th century home, but his powerful and unstable new robot, C.O.M.P.U.T.O., won't let the Legion pass through it!

Doc Magnus' responsometer goes out of control when connected to a Mother Box
name: C.O.M.P.U.T.O. The Conqueror

description:
General Notes

The title of this issue comes from Papa Legba, a figure in the belief system of Haitian Vodou or "voodoo". Although Papa Legba himself appears in the issue, the word "Legba" is never mentioned in the story itself and he is only referred to as "Attibon" and "Papa".
name: Legba

description: With the Flash confined to a wheelchair thanks to a broken leg, Keystone could soon become an open city for criminals everywhere. To prevent this, Flash enlists the aid of Jay Garrick, Impulse & Max Mercury to make it appear that the Scarlet Speedster is still in control. But The Suit sees through this charade and takes the opportunity to finish off Flash once & for all.
name: Emergency Stop part 2 of 3:Threads

description: The conclusion to "Ace of Killers!" Out of options and out of ammo, Tommy faces down the Mawzir in a battle for his very soul. But when all seems lost, someone with a few lives to spare might be able to help...
name: Ace of Killers, Part 6

description: Power Girl joins with Supergirl to stop the Extremists; Twilight's origin is revealed.
name: Blonde Justice
The Soldier: Book Two

description: John Irons and Amanda Quick look for the policemen who attacked them in issue #42, only to find themselves being questioned about a policeman's mysterious murder.
name: Fire

description: Doctor Tomorrow is dragged into the 1950s kicking and screaming! Despite Doc's heroic efforts in Korea and commie busting back in the states, "Tailgunner" Joe McCarthy sets his sights to expose Doc as a dyed-in-the-wook Communist. Besieged on all sides, Tomorrow is then betrayed by one of his closest allies, threatening his future technology and even his life!
name: Tomorrow Ends Today

description: You've heard rumors about them in the pages of X-O Manowar, now see one of their fiercest agents in action against the power of Ninjak! Prepare to evade a trap set by INQUEST!
Amok's on the hunt again, and Donovan's going to need WWII superhero Bravado's help to survive this fight!
name: The Past is Prologue

description:
Overview
So, you think you know it all? You think you know the story of Concrete's origin? Well, you don't know the whole story. For the first time, creator Paul Chadwick reveals the events around the transformation of speechwriter Ronald Lithgow into the seven-foot tall Concrete in their entirety, with the kinds of subtle, moving touches that could only come from his pen.

A stranger with a familiar face has come to Tarzan's African estate to seek help from the jungle lord: alien hordes from the moon have all but conquered the Earth of the far future, and only the Waziri remain! Tarzan and his son, Korak must accompany the stranger into the cave of Nu, and lead a battle in the 24th Century!
name: Tarzan vs. The Moon Men (Part 1 of 4)

description: The Penguin has returned to a life of crime, using an Egyptian falcon as a reason to renew his battle of wits with Batman and lure the Dark Knight into a deadly trap.
name: The Penguin Returns, Part Two - The Egyptian Falcon

description: Final Issue! Whisked away high over Gotham by a saucer-shaped craft, Batman experiences possibly his strangest adventure ever. Which of his foes is behind this deadly "close encounter" and can Batman survive long enough to counter a megalomaniac with that much power on hand?
name: Demon in the Sky

description: In an era with thought police, telepathic crime lords, and antigravity technology, can the legend of the Dark Knight survive? A hundred years in the future, Gotham City is a very different place, but it is still a very dark place--and a place in need of a protector.
name: The Incredible Adventures of Batman

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Catwoman and the Huntress end their team-up in a blaze of combat against Gotham's worst mobsters. Plus, Catwoman's relationship with Morland McShane takes a grim and unexpected turn.
name: The Headhunter: Bigger Game

description:
The Challengers' benefactor, Edward Sands, has mysteriously gone to Gotham City, where weird things are happening.

The Challengers assist Batman as time goes funny in Gotham City.
name: Time Fades Away

description: Flash has to look to the Speed Force for salvation when The Suit takes out his fellow speedsters, leaving the crippled Wally West to deal with it alone!
name: Emergancy Stop part 3 of 3

description:
The 10 year Anniversary issue. Set in a bar, drinking with John Constantine and just talking about the last 10 years.

This is a story where real world horror and the Hellblazer comics are blurred. What is Magic? What is fiction? These questions are asked.

There is also cameos from past and present (at the time) Hellblazer creators who interact with John. the famed and most talked about Cameo is the Alan Moore appearance in the Shadow. This is talked about because of the fact Alan Moore has mentioned meet John Constantine in the real world a few times.

By the end of this meta-fiction issue, we are left to decide if John is real? Is his stories, just stories? Will we come to the bar again once a month and drunk up and listen to him speak?

*CHEERS* clink cup with John Constantine
name: Desperately Seeking Something

description: Tim Hunter and John Constantine are reunited in a special 2-issue miniseries. Tim and his original mentor in magic are paired together for a tale of youth lost and adulthood found. When Tim discovers a locket containing a supernatural presence, he enlists John's aid to uncover its secrets, unaware that a relentless demon is hot on his heels.
name: Book One: Ascent

description: Bart has to deal with his pal Preston, who gets wounded as an innocent bystander to one of Impulse's fights. But Preston has bigger fish to fry--namely his mother and the state of her mental health.
name: Unhealed Wounds

description: Captain Marvel and Mary reach out to a classmate who is a burn victim.
name: Yeah--This Is A Face Only A Mother Could Love...

description:
Les Enfants Du Sang make their move on our heroes, but with Jesse in a voodoo-inspired trance, can Tulip and Cassidy hold down the fort on their own? Plus, a major reptile slithers onto the scene.

Jesse finally gets in touch with Genesis and learns the horrible secret of the Saint of Killers; Cassidy and Tulip have another little chat, and Cassidy loses his head to Les Enfants du Sang.
name: Snakes In The Grass

description: Tim Drake aka Robin is taken to Qurac with the aid of Nightwing as pilot. Robin is only planning on capturing Ulysses so that he can return the 11 year old general to Gotham - whilst hopefully avoiding the dangerous crossfire of mercenaries like Gunhawk, Hatchet, Deadline and NKVDemon.
name: Mission Creep

description: Coin collectors descend upon New York for a convention, and the police follow, suspecting a market for illegally smuggled gold from Nazi Germany. One collector's craving for ill-gotten gold proves fatal, and Lieutenant Burke and the Sandman immediately compete for clues.
name: The Cannon Act I of IV

description:
The Spectre’s quest finally causes him to look the one place he has neglected. Inside himself. There he finds secrets from the early days of Jim Corrigan and the Spectre.

The Spectre's crisis of conscience leads him on a quest through time and space.

When an old friend suggests that The Spectre and Jim Corrigan use their powers to see into the soul of a man on each other, new facts about each of their origins surface.
name: Within

description:
In "Talking with David '97," David brings Jack to a very special dinner party, one featuring the fallen heroes of the All-Star Squadron. The original Black Canary, Hourman, Mr. Terrific, Atom, Dr. Mid-Nite and the Red Bee all share their experiences with Jack--and offer some surprising revelations.

David and a group of dead heroes give advice to Jack over dinner.
name: Talking With David, '97

description: When a man-on-the-street interview garners a harsh reaction, Angela Chen finds herself with a potentially big story. Seems the man belongs to a witness protection program, and when his cover is blown, Superman and Angela have to find him before an Intergang-hired hitman does!
name: Stop the Presses!

description:
In the first of three self-contained issues, Spider is drawn into The City's corrupt political arena, leading to a terrible confrontation with the President of the United States...in a men's room. And Spider is assigned an assistant to keep him in line--but she's not what he expects.

The issue begins with Spider naked and writing (possibly never a good sign), He's then interrupted by his boss who wants his column now, Spider tells him to get off and that the column isn't due until a few days anyway. It's at that point, his boss tells him he's getting an assistant, he gets quite mad about that and stands up to go blast what he thinks will be some punk kid he can't work with with his Bowel Disruptor, but when he gets there...it's Channon Yarrow, an ex-stripper whom he had met before.

The two exchange a few brief words (basically Spider telling her everything he wants her to do), She comes back sometime later...this time, Spider's wearing pants. They discuss the world and more-so Spider's odd views on it as well as journalism etc.

Soon enough, the TV comes on with a message that the president will be coming to town. Spider immediately shouts out "LETS GO SEE THE PRESIDENT".

Spider and Channon then go out to town, he manages to get into the Presidents address and it isn't long before Spider snoops around and finds the president BEFORE the address..in the rest room of all places.

He's mumbling to himself about cheap Australian whores and having hard time peeing when Spider walks in, the two get into a war of words that eventually ends with Spider throwing him into a stall and using the "Bowel Disruptor" on him..set to "Prolapse".

Spider walks out and tells Channon they need to leave.

"Why?" she asked.

"HELP! THE PRESIDENT'S SHAT HIMSELF!" the Secret Service cried out.

Then Channon and Spider leave.
name: On the Stump

description: The carnival's in town…and it brings Hippolyta, Artemis, and Donna Troy something far more sinister than amusement in the form of Egg Fu! And on Olympus, Diana adjusts to her new existence as a goddess, while back on Earth, Donna Troy must deal with her ever more confusing life in the aftermath of GENESIS…and Diana's replacement as Wonder Woman makes her debut!
name: Shell Game

person_credits.name: David Mack
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist

description: Facing defeat at the hands of Ghaur and his men, the Heroes for Hire are helped out by Ant-Man who has secretly been serving the team!
name: Deviants attack!

description:
Franklin Richards has visions of being in a life raft as New York floods, while accompanied by a woman who ominously tells him of choices he must make. He wakes up in the Everglades where the Man-Thing has been watching over him. He inadvertently knocks his ball into the water, and it is snapped up by a hungry alligator. Franklin becomes angry, and using his powers destroys the reptile to retrieve the ball that is so important to him.

Elsewhere, Peter Parker views a television retrospective about the anniversary of the "deaths" of the Fantastic Four and the Avengers. In New York City, the Hulk screams in pain. And, yet somewhere else, something crashes to earth, obliterating an observatory, then taking the form of a woman.

As Franklin holds his ball, images of the Hulk, the Thing and Thor form within the globe, and the mystrious woman then appears. She confronts the Man-Thing, who is stricken with fear, and self-immolates, then collapses in the water.

In the New York of another universe, the members of the Fantastic Four become uneasy as Sue Storm Richards breaks down in tears.

Back in the swamp, the woman, Ashema, explains to Franklin that she is one of the Celestials, and he is the end result of an eons-long experiment. The experiment complete, Franklin must now decide which universe, the world he lives in or the world he's created for the 'dead' heroes, will be the one to continue. She transports the two of them into the pocket universe, where he sees the world he made. Ashema then teleports him into the bedroom of Reed and Sue Richards, who are shocked to meet the son they are unaware they had.
name: The Judgment

description: Parnival Plunder turns the city into Savage Land.
name: Urban Jungle (Chapter One): Bright Lights, Big Jungle

description:
Carl Shuffler, a mail clerk at a New York television station, is undergoing bizarre experiences. He feels like he's sleepwalking through his own life, while also feeling as if exists in a monstrous form. As he delivers mail to a newsanchor and her producer, brief contact causes her arm and his hands to burst into flame. Panicking, he flees the building.

Elsewhere, Spider-Man sits on the side of a building contemplating the odd missions he'd recently taken on. Falling debris gets his attention, and he swings up to the roof, where a messenger waits for him, offering his employer's business card labeled, "The Authority".

Meanwhile, in the surveillance chamber that is the lair of the man who calls himself the Authority, he exhorts his minions to gather a variety of data for him to assimilate. Assembling certain bits of his assistants' analyses, he concludes that Asgardian Norn Stones have fallen to Earth, making "stone-bearers" of Carl Shuffler and the Man-Thing, scrambling their personas in the process.

Unable to get a hold of their selves, both Carl and the Man-Thing, who somehow has gotten to New York, each try to make their way home.

Going to the address given to him, Spider-Man bursts in and finds the Authority waiting for him. He tells Spidey he must undertake a new mission in order to prevent the deaths of millions.

Meanwhile, the newsanchor, Tippi, visits the home of Carl Shuffler. Carl, unable to handle the wave of emotions from his nagging wife and the concerned Tippi, leaps out a window and onto the streets, where he somehow transforms into the Man-Thing. Spider-Man, Mrs. Shuffler and Tippi all converge on the scene. The Wall-Crawler tries to soothe the slime monster, who turns for an apparent attack. But part of the Man-Thing extends a crystal stone, which Spider-Man takes. Carl becomes himself again, fully in his right mind. Spidey, briefly overwhelmed by the power of the stone, drops it and it vanishes.

Observing from his lair, the Authority bemoans the loss of the stone, then considers the new mission for which he has been preparing Spider-Man.
name: Suspended Sentence

description:
The New Mutants have travelled into the future (to the present) and, meeting their older counterparts, get questions answered from their future selves. Illyana Rasputin teleports back to the others with her brother, Mikhail in tow. He says he threw himself into the vortex of time to try to save his sister's life in the past, and he wants help.

The present-day mutants confer: Sam Guthrie and Dani Moonstar decide the villainous Mikhail can't be trusted, and they attack.  The older mutants nearly defeat their young versions, but a suddenly more powerful Karma decides to help Mikhail keep his family together.  She possesses the older kids, and has Sunspot take out Sam.  Only the younger Rahne is left, uneasily knowing she must oppose Mikhail alone.
name: Family Matters

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Quicksilver and his Knights of Wundagore set up camp along the Hudson River. But no sooner are they settled into their castle, when the team faces a threat from Thundra, time-traveling warrior woman! But what has drawn Thundra to the present?
name: The Wrong Day To Start A New Life

description:
The biggest battle of the series so far.  Five Federation ships battle in space above the Theta Kalyb Colony.  Meanwhile the Federation has dropped off medical crew to help with the devastation on the planters surfaces.  While helping on the surface Gabrielle Carlotti goes to the site of a crashed Chakuun ship and find a loan survivor.  
 
In space Captain Pike and his crew plus the U.S.S. Nelson are the only ship left in the battle.  Even Captain Crowe's ship U.S.S. Achilles is destroyed. Things get worse until the Chakuun who was found by Carlotti goes back to her ship.  After reacting her ship she breaks off the attacked due to her changed perception on human changing after meeting Gabrielle.
name: The Fallen (Part Two)

description: Parent's day at the Academy brings the usual morass of secrets, awkward situations and...a deadly secret that could kill everyone in the building.

The chilling conclusion to this two-parter! The U.S.S. Voyager has been captured by a runaway computer that turns alien species into bizarre zoological exhibits! Now Captain Janeway races against time to save her ship and crew!
name: Leviathan, Part Two

description: Black Widow offers advice to Songbird and MACH-1 by telling them a tale of the first replacement Avengers.
name: Life Lessons
Blood Will Tell

description: Sabretooth ambushes Wolverine!
name: Alone in His Head

description:
Access returns from an adventure with Batman and Spider-Man and, reverting to his identity as Axel Asher, discovers he's missed his lunch date with his girlfriend, Ming. Not understanding how he lost several hours, he finds her between classes and Empire State University and apologizes, revealing his dual identity to her, but, still angry, she doubts him. At that moment, Mantis attacks the school, and Axel activates his costume. He teleports Ming to safety as Spider-Man tries to tackle Mantis. Juggernaut and Wonder Woman also enter the fray.

Working together, Spidey and Wonder Woman defeat the villians, who are then mysteriously teleported elsewhere. Access is then surprised to learn that Diana does not recall having met him, but he provides the means to return her to her native universe. She flies away, and Access soon encounters the rampaging Hulk, who exhibits his savage persona, not the mind of Bruce Banner, as Access would expect. He offers to return the Hulk to where he belongs, but the nervous Access has trouble opening a portal. To Access' confusion, the late Hal Jordan Green Lantern intervenes. As Green Lantern subdues the Hulk, Access sees a discarded newspaper, and realizes he gone back in time.

Access then transports Hulk to the American southwest of the Marvel Universe. The behemoth leaps away, stranding Access, so he opens another portal, only to find himself in the Old West where he meets Jonah Hex and the Two-Gun Kid. Access sends Two-Gun to his home dimension, then accompanies Hex to a saloon. There, Hex is confronted by a vengeful gunman. To save the lawman's life, Access pushes him through a portal, but loses him between worlds.

Access then appears in a devastated New York City, accosted by Sentinels. However, the Legion of Super-Heroes arrive to defend him.
name: No Time Like the Present!

description:
Sal puts pressure on Darcy to get the Senate off his back. She tells him that subtle plans are in motion, when is remains unhappy Darcy smashes the phone into one of her gardener's faces.  

David has packed his bag and walking out when Darcy pulls a gun on him and only misses his head when he ducks. She then tries to kiss him and when he rejects her violently the gun goes off again, she indicates that his past is not so innocent either and he has something dark in his past too.   

As David leaves he discovers he was shot in the forearm and collapses. Fran and Walsh pull up and take him to the hospital where he fills them in on Katchoo's location.     

In New York Katchoo is outraged that the dress picked out for her makes her look like Darcy.
name: Immortal Enemies

description: The story of Clius Petroneus, one of the Juris, who lived in ancient Rome.
name: The Book of Law, Chapter Five of Five: Clius/The Road To You, Being There: Part Five

description: Held captive by the Russians, Daredevil and Black Widow set aside their differences and align themselves to escape! Once freed from their bonds, the heroes try to take down the Russian Mafia. Daredevil recruits two Soviet allies.
name: Widow's Kiss (Part 3)
...Where Angels Fear to Tread...

description: We find out where the heck Woody has been. Quantum & Woody break up. But they aren't a couple... remember that.
name: Tock: David Warrant Is Not Dead

description: Nearly two decades from now, the United States of America are no more. Instead, the North American continent is run by a provisional government implemented by the man-made mutant hunters called Sentinels. The once-respected espionage agency, S.H.I.E.L.D., has become no more than a gestapo run by a man who was once among the country's greatest enemies. The only resistance to this despotic rule are small bands of freedom fighters scattered across the once-majestic landscape. Among them is a group of people who have never stopped fighting to save a world that has brutally persecuted them--the mutants known as the X-Men! Now Magneto, the X-Men's longtime arch-foe, calls upon them for help. But why would the man who has become one of the most hated criminals on the planet reach out to those who have sworn to defeat him? Perhaps because he needs them to find the former X-Man who, it seems, has not been seen in years--the man they call Wolverine!
name: Ill Winds
Too Late To Lock The Barn Door...!

description:
After blasting Deep Blue, Rhombus takes Aquaman for a ride. The others join in, and Koryak destroys the body Rhombus took over.

Senator Perkins is on a fact finding mission to learn more about the Atlantean trade business when Tsunami rushes by to come to her daughter's aid against Rhombus, causing him to drop everything and jump overboard in pursuit. Aquaman then uses his telepathy with the squids to block Rhombus's view and sending Debbie back to Poseidonis with two dolphins as Aquaman enters into the blacked out area to battle him. Koryak then finds the injured Debbie vowing to kill the person responsible, as Aquaman continues to battle Rhombus. Rhombus however sees the dome and all the ships and flies to wipe it out dragging Aquaman with him,before blowing up a ship with Aquaman on it and flying away.

Rhombus then experiences several memories where he remembers Atlan banished him learning the connection between Aquaman and Atlan with the intent of revenge while still believing Debbie to be his daughter.While Vulko meets with Dardan over Aquaman's choices with the two plotting against the king's rule for young Koryak to rule which Dolphin overhears. Tsnuami then saves Aquaman, as Neptune begins battling with Rhombus who insists he admits Debbie is his daughter before deciding on drowning him. Aquaman then rescues Neptune while Tsunami battles Rhombus before Koryak shows up destroying him with his hard water spear.
name: Bad Relations

description: Kyle Rayner, Aquaman and Wally West are in a dystopian alternate future, where Darkseid rules Earth! After a recap of what led to this horrible situation, it is found out that only a handful of heroes are fit (or close to being fit) to confront him and his forces! It seems that Earth is utterly lost. But once again, our heroes take the old phrase, no guts no glory, to thei hearts, and get ready to save the world again!
name: Rock of Ages, Part 4: Wasteland

description: Deadpool and Blind Al are stuck in an old Spider-man comic. While there Deadpool uses his image inducer to look like Peter Parker. He also runs into a younger Weasel and accidentally starts hm on his path of crime. They eventually, with the help of young Weasel get back to their own time.
name: With Great Power Comes Great Coincidence

description: On the trail of a vodoun loa possessing the citizens of New Orleans and filling them with a twisted hunger for human eyes, Mike still manages to find time for his budding relationship with Detective DeFilo.
name: The Buzz, Part 2

description: Stormwatch converges on a small time in Louisiana, legally, to investigate the shady dealings there. They learn that the soldiers there have been illegally gifted with superhuman organs. Stormwatch takes down the operation, which was also involved in eco-terrorism. Meanwhile, Henry Bendix is still alive and under the care of I.O.
name: Strange Weather, Three Of Three: A Storm Coming

description:
PKNA #12

Seconda stesura / Second Draft
name: Seconda stesura

description: Luse catches up with the serial killing cop Ed Kemper and finds out Jace's whereabouts
name: Four: Killer In Me Killer in You

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

description: A serial killer is stalking the streets of New York on All Hallow's Eve. And the only way that the ghostly hero Deadman can stop the murderer is by possessing the body of Green Lantern.
name: All Hallow's Eve

description: Boy takes off to locate her brother, who was last spotted in a secret detention camp in the heart of America, in part 1 of a 3-part story. But will the ex-Harlem cop race right into a trap set up by ultra-terrestrial archenemies?
name: Counting to None

description:
G. W. Bridge and two S.H.I.E.L.D. agents land on Muir Island, intending to recruit Kitty Pryde for a single mission: computers aboard the Helicarrier have become unresponsive, but they indicate that Kitty is the only user they can recognize.

Despite Pete Wisdom's wishes, Kitty agrees to aid S.H.I.E.L.D. as an intern agent. Dum-Dum Dugan and Countess Valentina brief Kitty on the situation, and she set to work, partnered with AI specialist intern Rigby Fallon. Before they get very far, Ogun reveals himself as the entity behind the out of control computers; his recent possession of Lady Deathstrike has taught him how to infect circuitry.

Ogun then causes the Helicarrier to drift dangerously through Manhattan, and, imitating Kitty, phones Wolverine to come to her aid, and into his trap.
name: The Calling

description: It's Trick-or-Treat time for the Resurrection Man as he winds up dead in a small town reported to be the sighting place of a mysterious Bigfoot-like creature called the Big Howler. For one man, this town may see the culmination of a lifetime's work; for his son, it's just another place for his father to be ridiculed. That is, unless Mitch's new power brings the urban legend to life.
name: Tricks or Treats
